                <h4>Executive Order of NOMASHE: Straw & Hole Classification</h4>
                <p><strong>Hole:</strong> A void with a single opening. Can be tiny or huge, but it ends without connecting to another opening.</p>
                <p><strong>Tunnel:</strong> A hole that connects two openings. Bigger than a regular hole, usually traversable.</p>
                <p><strong>Straw:</strong> A small tunnel. Essentially, a tunnel you can sip through. In short: a straw = a tiny tunnel = two holes connected.</p>
                <p>So basically, every straw is a tunnel, every tunnel has two holes, and every hole might someday wish it was a tunnel.</p>
